sentences: She studied with Norah de Kresz privately before she entered The Royal Conservatory of Music at the age of 19 in 1928.
She was a self-taught composer until she began studying with Willan in 1936.
After marrying in 1939, she subsequently turned down a scholarship to Juilliard.
She also left her teaching position at The Royal Conservatory of Music and did not return until 1954.
Blomfield Holt taught music history,  theory, composition and piano performance until she retired from the faculty in 1985.
In 1938 she won the Vogt Society Award for the best music composition for her Suite No. 1 for Violin and Piano.
Her Lyric Piece No. 2 was recorded by Jeremy Findlay and Elena Braslavsky in 2002.

sentences: Patricia Blomfield Holt (15 September 1910 – 5 June 2003) was a Canadian composer, pianist and music educator.

Her Suite No. 2 was described by London's Musical Times: "The language is frankly of the 19th century, and the forms are reminiscent of Schumann, but the material is handled with certainty and a nice sense of texture".
Born Patricia Blomfield in Lindsay, Ontario, Blomfield Holt began her career in her teenage years as a largely self-taught composer and pianist.
She studied and taught concurrently for the next ten years.
